# Handoff notes

When creating a handoff note (for this project or when the user asks for a handoff):

## Location and filename

- **Save under (The Satellite — M1 MacBook):** `/Users/joe/Library/Mobile Documents/iCloud~md~obsidian/Documents/Handoff/`
- **The Source (M4 Mini):** `/Volumes/HomeX/joemini/Library/Mobile Documents/iCloud~md~obsidian/Documents/Handoff/` — use the path for the machine you’re on.
- Do not create handoff notes in the project repo (e.g. no `HANDOFF.md` in repo root).
- **Filename:** Include project and timestamp so notes are unique and sortable, e.g. `Punkeye Pictures Landing handoff 2026-03-05 14-23.md`
- Ensure the Handoff folder exists before writing (e.g. `mkdir -p` the path above).

## Required metadata (top of note)

- **Sent from:** &lt;this Mac's hostname&gt; — from `hostname` (shorten to part before `.local` if desired).
- **Day & time:** &lt;date and time with timezone&gt; — e.g. `2026-03-05 14:23 PST` from `date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M %Z'`.

## Style (match this structure)

- **First line:** `**Sent from:** &lt;hostname&gt; · **Day & time:** &lt;date time zone&gt;`
- Use **### Section title — Subtitle** for main sections (e.g. `### Canada Council — Application Status`).
- Use **---** between major sections.
- Use bullet points with **bold label:** then description (e.g. `- **General version:** Invitation to…`).
- Use tables where useful (e.g. Section | File | Status).
- Include a **Key Documents** section with paths (e.g. `Fundraising/Canada Council/…`).
- When the session used **Cursor**, include **### Cursor — Chats since last handoff** (or **### Cursor — Chats since last handoff — Subtitle**) with:
  - **Previous handoff:** wikilink to the last `Handoff/…` note (or “none” / first of its kind).
  - **Chat subjects this session:** bullet list — each line: chat topic/title, workspace or repo if useful, one-line outcome or decision.
  - **Optional:** transcript reference `[title](uuid)` if the user provides it; **optional short excerpts** only if needed on the other Mac (full history does not sync automatically).
- End with **### Next Session — Suggested First Steps** (numbered list of concrete next actions).
- No top-level "# Handoff note" title; the first line is the metadata line above.
